   176→<script setup lang="ts">
   177→// Debug page for XmlEditor Component (MVP 4)
   178→// This page demonstrates the XmlEditor component in isolation
   179→// Tests: v-model binding, XML features, editor statistics
   180→
   181→useHead({
   182→  title: \'Monaco XML Editor Demo - OhMyDoc\',
   183→})
   184→
   185→// Reactive state
   186→const editorContent = ref(\'\')
   187→const isLoading = ref(false)
   188→const loadError = ref<string | null>(null)
   189→const sampleXml = ref(\'\')
   190→
   191→// Editor statistics computed from content
   192→const statistics = computed(() => {
   193→  const content = editorContent.value
   194→
   195→  return {
   196→    lineCount: content ? content.split(\'\
\').length : 0,
   197→    characterCount: content.length,
   198→    wordCount: content.trim() ? content.trim().split(/\\s+/).length : 0
   199→  }
   200→})
   201→
   202→// Load sample XML from /public/samples/cover-letter.xml
   203→async function loadSample() {
   204→  isLoading.value = true
   205→  loadError.value = null
   206→
   207→  try {
   208→    const response = await fetch(\'/samples/cover-letter.xml\')
   209→
   210→    if (!response.ok) {
   211→      throw new Error(`Failed to load sample: ${response.status} ${response.statusText}`)
   212→    }
   213→
   214→    const xmlContent = await response.text()
   215→    sampleXml.value = xmlContent
   216→    editorContent.value = xmlContent
   217→  }
   218→  catch (error) {
   219→    const errorMessage = error instanceof Error ? error.message : \'Unknown error occurred\'
   220→    loadError.value = `Failed to load sample XML: ${errorMessage}`
   221→  }
   222→  finally {
   223→    isLoading.value = false
   224→  }
   225→}
   226→
   227→// Clear editor content
   228→function clearEditor() {
   229→  editorContent.value = \'\'
   230→  loadError.value = null
   231→}
   232→
   233→// Handle editor errors
   234→function handleEditorError(error: string) {
   235→  loadError.value = error
   236→}
   237→
   238→// Load sample XML on component mount
   239→onMounted(() => {
   240→  loadSample()
   241→})
   242→</script>
